ia:content><media:content height="1080" medium="image" url="https://media-mbst-pub-ue1.s3.amazonaws.com/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-10/27d2d0b0-6205-11ee-bdf9-6468623b2ff2" width="1920"><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[2]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[Amazon / Engadget]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[The best early Amazon October Prime Day Deals for 2023 Echo Show 15]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[The best early Amazon October Prime Day Deals for 2023 Echo Show 15]]></media:title></media:content></item><item><title><![CDATA[Meta Quest 3 review: A bit of mixed reality makes for better VR]]></title><description type="html"><![CDATA[<div id="e9fdb8138e084e5eb024e6490ad0875c"><div style="left:0;width:100%;height:0;position:relative;padding-bottom:56.25%;"><iframe src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/GXfPXdUzFIg?rel=0" style="top:0;left:0;width:100%;height:100%;position:absolute;border:0;" allowfullscreen="" scrolling="no" data-embed-domain="www.youtube.com"></iframe></div></div><p> Meta Quest 3 证明了 Meta Ques 2 的划算。三年前，当这款 VR 耳机上市时，售价仅为 300 美元，对于大多数人来说，它是进入 VR 的完美门户。你不需要将它连接到任何东西，你只需打开它并进入虚拟现实。但去年 Meta 将价格提高到 400 美元，整个 VR 行业开始感觉非常乏味。</p><p>难怪售价 1,500 美元的 Meta Quest Pro 完全失败了——VR 已经陷入困境，很少有人真正需要如此昂贵的东西。</p><span id="end-legacy-contents"></span><p>售价 500 美元的 Quest 3 可能不会像 Quest 2 那样吸引那么多 VR 新手，但它仍然是 Meta 向前迈出的坚实一步。它具有您期望的所有升级，<em>并且</em>还具有全彩混合现实相机，让您可以在使用 VR 应用程序的同时查看现实世界的视图。稍微眯起眼睛，你几乎可以看到苹果在 Vision Pro 上的意图（尽管保真度要低得多）。</p><core-slideshow data-slideshowid="ccfb76fd-7d77-493d-a36f-bfb438e3bcdd"/><p>尽管有这些改进，Quest 3 让我更加惊叹 Meta 在 Quest 2 上所取得的成就，而 Quest 2 的原价仍然是 299 美元。对于新手来说，这款耳机仍然是最好的 VR 切入点，尽管我希望它现在能便宜一点。与此同时，一旦你爱上了 VR，Quest 3 就是合乎逻辑的升级。</p><p>它的特别之处在于：由于采用了一套新的薄饼镜头，它比 Quest 2 明显更薄、更轻。这些还有助于从新显示器产生更清晰的图像，每只眼睛可提供 2,064 x 2,208 像素。这甚至比今年早些时候令我们惊叹的 PlayStation VR 2 还要好。</p><p>据 Meta 称，Quest 3 还运行高通新的 Snapdragon XR2 Gen 2 芯片，该芯片的 GPU 处理能力是 Quest 2 的两倍。前面有两个用于混合现实的全彩摄像头，中间还有一个深度传感器，可以帮助绘制空间图并避开障碍物。这是值得注意的，因为 Meta 完全从 Quest Pro 中删除了这一功能。在存储方面，您可以选择售价 500 美元的 128GB 型号和售价 650 美元的 512GB 型号。 </p><figure><img src="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-10/5f8a72b3-665b-11ee-a79d-2a0059c150bc" data-crop-orig-src="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-10/5f8a72b3-665b-11ee-a79d-2a0059c150bc" style="height:1535px;width:2500px;" alt="元任务 3" data-uuid="306f31e2-fa81-367d-8a55-9e2c1609b0ea"><figcaption></figcaption><div class="photo-credit">摄影：Devindra Hardawar/Engadget</div></figure><p>现在来说说 Quest 3 所没有的：像 Quest Pro 一样，控制器上没有面部或眼球追踪功能，也没有摄像头。不过，至少他们已经摆脱了 Quest 2 游戏手柄上烦人的铃声。我认为您不会错过 Quest Pro 的任何功能 - 它们可能很酷，但开发人员还没有真正利用它们。</p><p> Meta 已经证明它可以制作一款可靠的独立 VR 耳机，但它真的能为每个人带来混合现实吗？这似乎是 Quest 3 背后的驱动力。苹果的 Vision Pro 向我们展示了空间计算的真正有前途的愿景，数字世界和物理世界可以轻松共存。但那东西也要花费 3,499 美元。试图以一小部分的价格完成类似的事情似乎是不可能的。</p><p> Quest 3 在混合现实方面的尝试远非完美——彩色摄像头提供了模糊、像素化的世界视图，就好像你处于毒品引起的迷雾中一样。但它仍然非常有用。只需双击 Quest 3 侧面即可在沉浸式 VR 和现实世界之间切换。</p><p>我最终经常使用它来检查文本和 Slack 消息、从计算机中获取信息以及与周围的人聊天。在过去，做任何这些事情都需要完全取下耳机，或者翻转遮阳板。 </p><figure><img src="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-10/5f8a72b1-665b-11ee-b2ee-c98813fbdb49" data-crop-orig-src="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-10/5f8a72b1-665b-11ee-b2ee-c98813fbdb49" style="height:1463px;width:2500px;" alt="元任务 3" data-uuid="afb5a898-f2f8-3566-a787-f3c39825997a"><figcaption></figcaption><div class="photo-credit">摄影：Devindra Hardawar/Engadget</div></figure><p> Quest 3 不仅仅让您看到现实世界：您还可以执行一些基本的混合现实多任务处理。您可以在您面前的半透明虚拟托盘上排列最多三个窗口 Quest 应用程序，例如 WhatsApp 和 Quest Store。更好的是，您可以将该托盘移动到空间的任何位置。这不是我经常使用的东西，但事实上，我<em>可以</em>创建这个环境，将其锚定到现实世界中的特定点，然后在它周围走动，这让我大吃一惊。</p><p> Quest 3 还让每个虚拟元素看起来都异常清晰。在耳机中查看 WhatsApp 聊天内容与在游戏显示器上查看没有什么不同。不过，Meta 仍然需要努力让 Quest 的应用程序变得更加有用：我只能通过笨拙地敲击 Quest 的虚拟键盘、留下语音消息或从耳机附加媒体来回复 WhatsApp 聊天。 （我们只希望马克·扎克伯格展示的<a data-i13n="cpos:1;pos:1" href="https://www.instagram.com/p/Cwfql7thwVl/?utm_source=ig_embed&amp;utm_campaign=embed_video_watch_again">桌面虚拟键盘</a>能够真正成为现实。） </p><figure><img src="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-10/4885ee20-66b3-11ee-959e-5df2e0b142a7" data-crop-orig-src="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-10/4885ee20-66b3-11ee-959e-5df2e0b142a7" style="height:1152px;width:1437px;" alt="任务 3 混合现实" data-uuid="37adb4b8-e061-39de-87ae-323719e60190"><figcaption>从我的家庭房间瞥见 Quest 3 的混合现实视图。</figcaption><div class="photo-credit">摄影：Devindra Hardawar/Engadget</div></figure><p> Quest 3 也标志着我第一次真正喜欢使用 Meta 的手指追踪。当它<a data-i13n="cpos:2;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/2019-09-27-oculus-quest-hand-tracking-hands-on.html">出现在最初的 Quest 上</a>时，这是一个有趣的功能，但它并不总是准确的，所以我更喜欢使用 Quest 的控制器。现在，借助深度传感器和全彩摄像头，Quest 3 在识别每个手指手势方面做得更好。我发现自己更频繁地让控制器休息，因为通过滑动和虚拟指向来浏览应用程序非常容易。</p><p>鉴于 Quest 2 在作为独立 VR 耳机方面的出色表现，我对 Quest 3 甚至更好并不感到惊讶。由于 RAM 增加，所有内容加载速度都更快。控制器感觉更加精确，特别是对于需要精确度的游戏，例如即将推出的<em>Samba de Amigo</em>和 VR 主流<em>Beat Saber</em> 。 </p><figure><img src="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-10/5f8a72b0-665b-11ee-aa6d-e96e348da898" data-crop-orig-src="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-10/5f8a72b0-665b-11ee-aa6d-e96e348da898" style="height:1610px;width:2500px;" alt="元任务 3" data-uuid="fc7c165d-a4fe-390f-bf4d-f6e939923610"><figcaption></figcaption><div class="photo-credit">摄影：Devindra Hardawar/Engadget</div></figure><p> Quest 3 更高分辨率的显示屏也使游戏看起来比 Quest 2 好得多，但更令我印象深刻的是少数针对其更快的硬件进行了优化的游戏。由于其极其细致的纹理和角色模型， <em>《Red Matter 2》</em>看起来几乎就像一款成熟的 PC VR 游戏。 Kurzgesagt 游戏<em>《Out of Scale》</em>让我感觉自己就像生活在其精美的 YouTube 动画视频之一中。</p><p> Quest 3 用户仍然可以访问同样适用于 Quest 2 的数百款游戏，但很高兴看到一些新游戏与新硬件一起推出。看起来还没有任何东西是 Quest 3 独有的，但这很容易改变。目前，我预计新游戏将会有额外的打磨，而 Quest 2 将获得更基本的体验。</p><p>我没有机会尝试<em>First Encounters</em> ，这是<a data-i13n="cpos:3;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/meta-quest-3-hands-on-a-proper-successor-to-the-most-popular-vr-headset-173750489.html">我们在最初预览</a>期间展示的 Quest 3 混合现实教程，但我希望更多的开发人员开始为 Quest 3 构建类似的体验。有一些真正的“混合现实” ” 已经有了一些游戏，比如<em>《Zombies Noir》</em>和<em>《Figmin XR》</em> ，但它们大多只是有趣的实验，而不是任何真正具有开创性的东西。 Quest 3 仍有空间提供 Magic Leap 和 HoloLens 等设备最初承诺的那种现实扭曲体验。</p><p>在测试 Quest 3 一周后，我注意到了一些令人惊讶的事情：这是第一款在使用时不会让我感到受困的耳机。由于现实世界很容易进入，所以我坐在 Netflix 上观看电影或 YouTube 上的 360 度视频感觉更舒服。而且由于其更轻的框架和额外的眼镜空间，我还可以比以前玩更长时间的 VR 游戏。</p><p>我只希望 Quest 3 的电池续航时间更长一些。根据您正在做的事情，它可以持续两到三个小时，就像 Quest 2 一样。至少您仍然可以在为耳机充电时使用它，并且在连接到 PC 时也能保持供电以获得更强大的体验，比如<em>谷歌地球VR</em> 。 </p><figure><img src="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-10/5f8a72b4-665b-11ee-afbf-71b1ce207cb2" data-crop-orig-src="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-10/5f8a72b4-665b-11ee-afbf-71b1ce207cb2" style="height:1464px;width:2500px;" alt="元任务 3" data-uuid="068c74ec-c242-3ec8-843c-4aae27bb7ca7"><figcaption></figcaption><div class="photo-credit">摄影：Devindra Hardawar/Engadget</div></figure><p>如果您看过我对 PlayStation VR 2 的评论，您就会知道我对 VR 目前的状况非常矛盾。耳机变得越来越好，但游戏和行业却停滞不前。至少，对于 VR 新手来说，Meta Quest 3 似乎是比 550 美元的 PlayStation VR 2 更好的选择。它价格昂贵，但它无需 PlayStation 5 即可提供稳定的 VR。虽然它不是 Vision Pro，但 Quest 3 的表现是混合的。现实使它成为您在 VR 蜜月结束后很可能仍会使用的耳机。</p><p>如果 500 美元的耳机太贵，我相信您可以廉价找到二手的 Quest 2。</p>本文最初发表在 Engadget 上：https://www.engadget.com/meta-quest-3-review-mixed-reality-vr-150009788.html?src=rss]]>; </description><link/><![CDATA[https://www.engadget.com/meta-quest-3-review-mixed-reality-vr-150009788.html?src=rss]]><source_id> engadget_479</source_id><guid ispermalink="false"> af6308d0-2aa7-4c09-aae9-c71e83695e48</guid><dc:creator>德文德拉·哈达瓦尔</dc:creator><source/><![CDATA[Engadget]]><dc:publisher>恩杰特</dc:publisher><dc:rightsholder>恩杰特</dc:rightsholder><pubDate>Mon, 09 Oct 2023 15:00:09 +0000</pubDate><ingested> 1696864108</ingested><modified> 2023-10-09T15:08:34+00:00 </modified><category><![CDATA[Media]]></category><category><![CDATA[Technology & Electronics]]></category><category><![CDATA[Arts & Entertainment]]></category><category><![CDATA[site|engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[provider_name|Engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[region|US]]></category><category><![CDATA[language|en-US]]></category><category><![CDATA[author_name|Devindra Hardawar]]></category><media:content height="1442" medium="image" url="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-10/5f8a72b0-665b-11ee-bf5f-4b93668c120f" width="2500"><media:keywords>标题</media:keywords><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[1]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[ ]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[ ]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[ ]]></media:title></media:content><media:content height="1442" medium="image" url="https://media-mbst-pub-ue1.s3.amazonaws.com/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-10/5f8a72b0-665b-11ee-bf5f-4b93668c120f" width="2500"><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[2]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[Photo by Devindra Hardawar/Engadget]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[Meta Quest 3]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[Meta Quest 3]]></media:title></media:content></item><item><title><![CDATA[The best smart speakers for 2023]]></title><description type="html"><![CDATA[<p>语音助手现在无处不在——在你的手机上、你的电视上，甚至可能在你的厨房用具上。但人们与 Siri、Alexa 和 Google Assistant 互动的最常见方式之一是通过智能扬声器，而且现在有各种不同价位的此类设备。拥有始终监听唤醒词的智能家居设备也有缺点，因为向亚马逊、苹果和谷歌提供更多个人信息可能是一个值得怀疑的决定。也就是说，所有这些公司都让管理数据的使用方式变得更加容易——你可以选择不让人工审查你的一些语音查询，而且使用各种数字助理来管理和删除你的历史记录也更简单。</p><p>好消息是，现在是购买智能扬声器的最佳时机，特别是如果您是音乐迷。尽管有很多好处，最初的 Amazon Echo 和 Google Home 设备听起来并不好。另一方面，Sonos 制造了音质出色的 WiFi 连接扬声器，但缺乏任何语音控制智能功能。</p><span id="end-legacy-contents"></span><p>现在一切都变了。 Sonos 于 2022 年发布了自己的语音助手，并在其最新的扬声器上支持 Alexa。与此同时，谷歌和亚马逊通过最新的扬声器在音质方面取得了巨大的进步。即使是像 Echo Dot 和 Nest Mini 这样的低端型号听起来也比早期版本要好得多。随着这些扬声器的日益普及，现在有比以往更多的选择。让我们来看看我们精选的不同价位和不同用途的最佳智能扬声器。</p><h2>选择助手<strong>：Google vs. Alexa</strong></h2><p>大多数人应该做的第一件事是决定他们想要使用什么语音助手。 Google Assistant 和亚马逊的 Alexa 都是得到良好支持的选项，并且不断发展，新功能不断添加。几年前，Alexa 与更多的智能家居设备配合使用，但目前，基本上任何值得购买的智能设备都可以同时使用这两种设备。</p><p>这主要是个人喜好的问题。如果您已经在 Android 手机上使用 Google Assistant，那么坚持使用 Google Assistant 是有意义的。不过，虽然 Alexa 不太擅长回答常识性问题，但它可以很好地与 Google 帐户中的日历等内容同步。它也可以与最广泛的智能家居设备配合使用。如果您从未使用过<a data-i13n="cpos:1;pos:1;elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:;elmt:;" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsImxhbmRpbmdVcmwiOiJodHRwczovL2FwcHMuYXBwbGUuY29tL3VzL2FwcC9hbWF6b24tYWxleGEvaWQ5NDQwMTE2MjAiLCJjb250ZW50VXVpZCI6IjIyZTNmMGI3LWMxNzktMzkyYS04MjFjLWU2ZGY1M2MyODBhNiJ9&amp;signature=AQAAARYWVaYBWoXE3saOh9reSP5jBvl5JqgaMir5u_WYF0GM&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fapps.apple.com%2Fus%2Fapp%2Famazon-alexa%2Fid944011620">Alexa</a>或<a data-i13n="cpos:2;pos:1;elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:;elmt:;" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsImxhbmRpbmdVcmwiOiJodHRwczovL3BsYXkuZ29vZ2xlLmNvbS9zdG9yZS9hcHBzL2RldGFpbHM_aWQ9Y29tLmdvb2dsZS5hbmRyb2lkLmFwcHMuZ29vZ2xlYXNzaXN0YW50JmhsPWVuX1VTJmdsPVVTIiwiY29udGVudFV1aWQiOiIyMmUzZjBiNy1jMTc5LTM5MmEtODIxYy1lNmRmNTNjMjgwYTYifQ&amp;signature=AQAAAdocdFrFh3jxXbyI2jt8pzj7IYj1eQKc51OO9U0yOHE0&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fplay.google.com%2Fstore%2Fapps%2Fdetails%3Fid%3Dcom.google.android.apps.googleassistant%26hl%3Den_US%26gl%3DUS">Google Assistant</a> ，您可以将它们的应用程序下载到您的智能手机上，并在购买扬声器之前花一些时间进行测试。</p><h2>索诺斯与苹果</h2><p>如果您购买带有麦克风的 Sonos 设备，您还可以使用<a data-i13n="cpos:3;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/sonos-voice-control-assistant-for-music-200538441.html">该公司自己的语音助手</a>，由 Giancarlo Esposito 配音。它纯粹专注于音乐控制，因此您不会用它来执行发送消息或询问天气预报等操作。但作为音乐助手，Sonos 语音控制通常相当快速且可靠。</p><p>至于 Apple，您不会惊讶地发现 HomePod 和 HomePod mini 是市场上唯一兼容 Siri 的扬声器。苹果的 Siri 因不如 Alexa 或 Google Assistant 智能而闻名，但它完全能够处理常见的语音查询，例如回答问题、控制智能家居设备、发送消息、拨打电话和流媒体音乐。从技术上讲，Siri 和苹果的 HomeKit 技术并不像竞争对手那样适用于那么多智能家居设备，但找到兼容的设备并不难。在过去的几年里，苹果无疑改进了 Siri 的功能，提供了方便的功能，例如利用 HomePod 和 HomePod Mini 中内置温度传感器的对讲工具和例程。</p><h2> 50 美元以下最佳智能音箱：Amazon Echo Dot </h2><p><core-commerce id="d9b8d32fabd14ba39688ca99f80af4ce" data-type="product-list"></core-commerce></p><p>大多数人进入智能音箱世界的切入点都不会是昂贵的设备。亚马逊的第四代<a data-i13n="cpos:4;pos:1;elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Amazon;elmt:;" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsInN0b3JlSWQiOiI2NmVhNTY3YS1jOTg3LTRjMmUtYTJmZi0wMjkwNGVmZGU2ZWEiLCJsYW5kaW5nVXJsIjoiaHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYW1hem9uLmNvbS9kcC9CMDlCOFYxTFozP3RhZz1nZGd0MGMtcC1vLWQ2LTIwIiwiY29udGVudFV1aWQiOiIyMmUzZjBiNy1jMTc5LTM5MmEtODIxYy1lNmRmNTNjMjgwYTYifQ&amp;signature=AQAAAZXNEHk7FsGNE_XvtNGqcNRKg4X5smBOvwFOgWVpzaOU&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2Fdp%2FB09B8V1LZ3%3F">Echo Dot</a>和谷歌的<a data-i13n="cpos:5;pos:1;elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Walmart;elmt:;" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=3719d8d4-5edd-4817-998a-91f3229e7323&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Walmart&amp;&amp;signature=AQAAAWI09cTB1paP_8rNk0Y7QX-pWjYPXnnM13p5n65pcwPv&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.walmart.com%2Fip%2FGoogle-Nest-Mini-2nd-Generation-Chalk%2F751612012">Nest Mini</a>是最明显的起点，有两个重要原因。第一，它们很便宜：Nest Mini 和 Echo Dost 的售价都是 50 美元。二是他们有能力。尽管价格低廉，这些扬声器实际上可以完成与更大、更昂贵的设备相同的功能。</p><p> Google Nest Mini 于 2019 年底发布，但亚马逊去年刚刚更新了 Echo Dot。对于大多数人来说，Echo Dot 是最好的小型智能扬声器。亚马逊不断改进其 Echo 设备系列的音频性能，Echo Dot 也不例外。它产生的声音比我对 50 美元扬声器的预期要响亮、清晰得多。 Nest Mini 听起来不错，非常适合在卧室里聆听，同时为新的一天做好准备，但 Echo Dot 是一款更好的通用音乐聆听设备。</p><p>从设计角度来看，亚马逊推出了最新的 Echo Dot，打破了常规。新款 Dot 的形状像一个小地球仪，而不是像 Nest Mini 那样的小冰球。它比 Nest Mini 大得多，但这样的尺寸为它提供了容纳高端音频组件的空间。虽然大部分情况下是免提的，但 Dot 将物理音量按钮和静音开关保留在顶部，以及一个用于激活 Alexa 语音控制的按钮。虽然 Dot 看起来不像 Nest Mini 那样时尚，但拥有物理按钮可以更轻松地调节音量和使麦克风静音。我确实希望 Dot 有一种方法可以物理暂停音乐；在 Nest Mini 上，如果您点击设备的中间，音乐就会停止。</p><p>总的来说，Dot 对于大多数人来说是最好的预算选择，但我会毫不犹豫地推荐 Nest Mini 作为另一个经济实惠的智能扬声器选择。与 Alexa 相比，我通常更喜欢使用 Google Assistant，任​​何有同感的人都应该购买 Nest Mini。 Dot 的听起来确实明显更好，所以如果您打算定期听音频，那么这可能是正确的选择。但是，如果您只打算在早上准备时使用它来播放一首快歌或播客，只需选择您最喜欢的助手并从那里开始即可。</p><h2> 100 美元以下最佳智能音箱：Amazon Echo </h2><p><core-commerce id="4071c4bc3ab14a62b2e309bc135efb14" data-type="product-list"></core-commerce></p><p>亚马逊、苹果和谷歌都有 100 美元的智能音箱：分别是第四代<a data-i13n="cpos:6;pos:1;elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Amazon;elmt:;" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsInN0b3JlSWQiOiI2NmVhNTY3YS1jOTg3LTRjMmUtYTJmZi0wMjkwNGVmZGU2ZWEiLCJsYW5kaW5nVXJsIjoiaHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYW1hem9uLmNvbS9kcC9CMDg1SEs0S0w2P3RhZz1nZGd0MGMtcC1vLWQ2LTIwIiwiY29udGVudFV1aWQiOiIyMmUzZjBiNy1jMTc5LTM5MmEtODIxYy1lNmRmNTNjMjgwYTYifQ&amp;signature=AQAAATdcQZxdYwTZKlKR3f8wqWL47-eHL5SKRgMmwrEYltFC&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2Fdp%2FB085HK4KL6%3F">Echo</a> 、 <a data-i13n="cpos:7;pos:1;elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Walmart;elmt:;" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=3719d8d4-5edd-4817-998a-91f3229e7323&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Walmart&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsInN0b3JlSWQiOiIzNzE5ZDhkNC01ZWRkLTQ4MTctOTk4YS05MWYzMjI5ZTczMjMiLCJsYW5kaW5nVXJsIjoiaHR0cHM6Ly93d3cud2FsbWFydC5jb20vaXAvSG9tZVBvZC1taW5pLVNwYWNlLUdyYXkvODEwNzQ2OTYxIiwiY29udGVudFV1aWQiOiIyMmUzZjBiNy1jMTc5LTM5MmEtODIxYy1lNmRmNTNjMjgwYTYifQ&amp;signature=AQAAAXA5tlqyG6X6C9ACOSTnyb27FaC-pkRyIPk1k08C52Vf&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.walmart.com%2Fip%2FHomePod-mini-Space-Gray%2F810746961">HomePod mini</a>和<a data-i13n="cpos:8;pos:1;elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Walmart;elmt:;" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=3719d8d4-5edd-4817-998a-91f3229e7323&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Walmart&amp;&amp;signature=AQAAAfTf66g1NcLyueHahQ7Wo_B-ftmspS_GfKNyJWMUNylN&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.walmart.com%2Fip%2FGoogle-Nest-Audio-Smart-Speaker-with-Google-Assistant-Chalk%2F778990339">Nest Audio</a> 。这三个公司都声称具有卓越的音频质量，因此对于很多人来说，这些扬声器将是 Echo Dot 和 Nest Mini 等小型扬声器与 Sonos Era 100 等更大、更昂贵的型号之间的最佳选择。</p><p>亚马逊再次超越了自己的实力。与 Dot 一样，最新的 Echo 也经过了彻底重新设计，新的内部结构也是以音乐为中心而设计的。它结合了一个 3 英寸低音扬声器和两个 0.8 英寸高音扬声器——比 Nest Audio 或 HomePod mini 更先进的设置。 （Google Nest Audio 使用一个 3 英寸低音扬声器，但只有一个 0.75 英寸高音扬声器，而 Apple HomePod mini 则使用一个“全频”驱动器和两个无源散热器。）</p><p>实际上，这意味着 Echo 明显比 Nest Audio 或 HomePod mini 响亮，并且比竞争对手更适合播放充满房间的声音。它还提供令人印象深刻的低音重击和强大的中频。事实上，我对扬声器的主要抱怨是高音不够清脆。将 Echo 与 Era 100 进行比较，100 听起来更加活泼，而 Echo 则显得有点浑浊。不过，100 的价格是 Echo 的两倍多。</p><p>虽然 Echo 扬声器可能在音量和低音方面击败 Nest Audio 和 HomePod mini，但谷歌和苹果的扬声器也是不错的选择。 HomePod mini 是三款扬声器中最安静的，但它在整个音频频谱中听起来仍然很平衡。低音不是太自信，但鉴于其微小的尺寸（它是迄今为止这三个扬声器中最小的），其存在感比我预期的要强。</p><p>如果您使用的是 iPhone 11 或更新机型，它还有一些不错的好处。得益于最近 iPhone 中的 U1“超宽带”芯片，HomePod mini 可以判断附近是否有手机，这使得将音乐从手机传递到扬声器（反之亦然）变得非常简单。 HomePod mini 的播放控件也会自动弹出，如果扬声器当前未播放，手机的锁定屏幕将显示音乐建议。设置也非常简单——只需将 iPhone 或 iPad 靠近扬声器，它就会自动启动该过程。</p><p>谷歌的 Nest Audio 听起来也相当好听。它的声音比 HomePod mini 稍大一些，并且低音更强。它的整体功率和表现力不如 Echo，但 100 美元的价格，它是一款平衡性良好的扬声器，应该可以满足大多数人的需求。</p><p>如果您想要更大的音量或渴望更身临其境的体验，所有这三个扬声器都支持立体声配对。只需 200 美元，两台 Echo 就能让整个大房间充满高品质的声音和足够的低音，足以为派对提供动力。一对 HomePod mini 或 Nest Audio 扬声器的功能不是那么强大，但如果您是一个更热心的听众，那么它可以带来很大的升级。工作日期间，一对 Nest Audio 或 HomePod 迷你扬声器放在我的办公桌上听起来很棒。我不需要压倒性的音量，但可以欣赏立体声分离度。其中两个扬声器一起可以轻松为更大的生活空间提供动力，尽管如果优先考虑音量，Echo 是更好的选择。</p><p>在这里，我也认为选择最适合您家中以及与其他小工具配合使用的智能助手可能是最重要的因素 - 但考虑到 Alexa 的无处不在和新 Echo 的卓越音质，它是这个价位上最好的智能扬声器。</p><h2>最佳中端智能音箱：Sonos Era 100 </h2><p><core-commerce id="25a95ee9632047bdbbbbb900dbf8b94a" data-type="product-list"></core-commerce></p><p>如果你对音乐只是一时的兴趣，那么 Echo Dot 和 Nest Mini 并不能真正满足你的需求。花更多的钱升级到在设计时考虑到音频质量的扬声器是我做出的最佳决定之一。多年来，我一直没有合适的家庭音乐解决方案，但最终，适度的投资让我的生活变得更加愉快。</p><p>多年来，Sonos One 一直是我的最爱，它结合了合理的价格、良好的音质和大量有用的功能，如简单的多房间音频、立体声配对以及与大量服务的兼容性。今年，Sonos 用<a data-i13n="cpos:9;pos:1;elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Sonos;elmt:;" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=1e71dc69-0ad7-47e7-abf5-dc3926557fa3&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Sonos&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsInN0b3JlSWQiOiIxZTcxZGM2OS0wYWQ3LTQ3ZTctYWJmNS1kYzM5MjY1NTdmYTMiLCJsYW5kaW5nVXJsIjoiaHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuc29ub3MuY29tL2VuLXVzL3Nob3AvZXJhLTEwMCIsImNvbnRlbnRVdWlkIjoiMjJlM2YwYjctYzE3OS0zOTJhLTgyMWMtZTZkZjUzYzI4MGE2In0&amp;signature=AQAAAZ2QTRvlnA5n8O6YgARV32cka-FgDMGabeYoGRrBpYQW&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.sonos.com%2Fen-us%2Fshop%2Fera-100">Era 100</a>取代了 One，这是一款售价 250 美元的扬声器，几乎在您能想到的所有方面都有所改进。最重要的是，它使用了一种新的扬声器阵列，其中包括两个高音扬声器（而不是只有一个）以及一个大 25% 的低音扬声器。最终的结果是，Era 100 在音质方面轻而易举地超越了 One，具有令人印象深刻的低音、令人惊讶的巨大音量以及由于额外的高音扬声器而提高的高端清晰度。</p><p>除了音质之外，还有很多其他改进。 Era 100 使用内置麦克风更轻松地进行 Trueplay 调音，从而根据您放置的位置优化扬声器的输出。以前，您必须使用 iPhone 在房间里走动并挥舞手机才能优化您的 Sonos 扬声器，但现在这个过程要简单得多。 Era 100 还包括通过 USB-C 端口的线路输入，并且当您只想快速将设备连接到扬声器时还具有蓝牙功能。令人遗憾的是，您需要购买适配器才能将转盘或其他音频设备连接到 Era 100，但由于 One 根本不支持线路输入，我仍然很高兴它是一种选择。</p><p>还有一些其他小而扎实的改进，例如重新设计的顶部控件，可以更轻松地跳过曲目，以及麦克风静音开关，可以切断麦克风的电源以提供额外的安全性。与 One 一样，在这里设置 Alexa 或 Sonos 语音助手很容易，但 Era 100<em>不</em>支持 Google Assistant - 因此，如果您以前使用 Sonos 扬声器并依赖 Google，那么您很不幸地不走运这里。不过，除了这一变化之外，Era 100 是一款出色的全能性能产品。它本身就是一款很棒的扬声器，如果您想构建多房间音频设置，它也是一个很好的起点。</p><p> Amazon Echo Studio 仍然是一款音质出色的扬声器，价格为 199 美元，也比 Era 100 便宜很多。如果您想节省一些现金，或者您的智能家居生态系统中已经拥有一堆其他 Echo 设备，那么将其作为更高质量音乐播放的扬声器是有意义的。但考虑到今年秋天它就已经上市四年了，我认为选择一款能够获得更长时间支持和更新的新设备是有意义的。</p><h2>最适合音乐爱好者的智能音箱：Sonos Five </h2><p><core-commerce id="a60083cdb64d44758943efa1a26eb1e4" data-type="product-list"></core-commerce></p><p>尽管 Era 100 和 Echo Studio 非常出色，但您能从它们中获得的功能也有限。如果您渴望更多的低音、清晰度和立体声分离度，550 美元的<a data-i13n="cpos:10;pos:1;elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Sonos;elmt:;" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=1e71dc69-0ad7-47e7-abf5-dc3926557fa3&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Sonos&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsInN0b3JlSWQiOiIxZTcxZGM2OS0wYWQ3LTQ3ZTctYWJmNS1kYzM5MjY1NTdmYTMiLCJsYW5kaW5nVXJsIjoiaHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuc29ub3MuY29tL2VuLXVzL3Nob3AvZml2ZSIsImNvbnRlbnRVdWlkIjoiMjJlM2YwYjctYzE3OS0zOTJhLTgyMWMtZTZkZjUzYzI4MGE2In0&amp;signature=AQAAAR25cLMb2vxNkMKEVe6NeoOcX395yZzkj30eSdpml_uG&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.sonos.com%2Fen-us%2Fshop%2Ffive">Sonos Five</a>是此列表中音质最好的智能扬声器。它具有 Era 100 的许多便利性，并且听起来比任何其他 Sonos 扬声器都要好。它听起来也比 Echo Studio 和谷歌目前销售的任何产品都要好得多。</p><p> That said, the Five stretches our definition of a smart speaker here because it doesn&#39;t have a built-in voice assistant. But it&#39;s so good at music playback that it&#39;s worth recommending you pick one up along with an Echo Dot or Nest Mini. Both of those speakers work with Sonos, so you can use voice commands to control the Five just as you would a dedicated Alexa or Google Assistant device. Sonos also refreshed the speaker two years ago with a new wireless radio as well as more memory and a faster processor. This means it should stay current and work with future Sonos software updates for years to come.</p><p> Since we&#39;re talking &quot;best&quot; here, I&#39;m going to go ahead and recommend that true music junkies splash out on two Five speakers and pair them in stereo. Put simply, it&#39;s the most enjoyable experience I&#39;ve had listening to music in years; I found myself picking up new details while listening to albums I&#39;ve heard over and over again. It&#39;s a wonderful experience and worth saving for if you&#39;re a music lover. I didn&#39;t know what I was missing until I tried the Five.</p><p> The Sonos <a data-i13n="cpos:11;pos:1;elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Sonos;elmt:;" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=1e71dc69-0ad7-47e7-abf5-dc3926557fa3&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Sonos&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsInN0b3JlSWQiOiIxZTcxZGM2OS0wYWQ3LTQ3ZTctYWJmNS1kYzM5MjY1NTdmYTMiLCJsYW5kaW5nVXJsIjoiaHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuc29ub3MuY29tL2VuLXVzL3Nob3AvZXJhLTMwMCIsImNvbnRlbnRVdWlkIjoiMjJlM2YwYjctYzE3OS0zOTJhLTgyMWMtZTZkZjUzYzI4MGE2In0&amp;signature=AQAAAVjDDSsafMZzXOPRzL6yDO_3xbdyYsxSHlScfT0ot5w0&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.sonos.com%2Fen-us%2Fshop%2Fera-300">Era 300</a> , also recently released, is a $450 speaker that supports Dolby Atmos spatial audio from Apple Music and Amazon Music Unlimited. I&#39;ve found that the quality of spatial audio mixes can be very hit or miss, but the good news is that the Era 300 sounds outstanding whether it&#39;s playing back Atmos content or just standard tracks. It&#39;s not quite as good as the Sonos Five, but it does have built-in microphones for voice assistants and easy Trueplay tuning as well as Bluetooth and the redesigned controls on the Era 100. Again, the main downside is that Google Assistant isn&#39;t supported here.</p><p> Finally, if you&#39;re an Apple Music user or have a lot of Apple hardware in your home, the second-generation <a data-i13n="cpos:12;pos:1;elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Apple;elmt:;" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=4130e2f0-a14f-4c5e-bdab-cd52ac7d8e79&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Apple&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsInN0b3JlSWQiOiI0MTMwZTJmMC1hMTRmLTRjNWUtYmRhYi1jZDUyYWM3ZDhlNzkiLCJsYW5kaW5nVXJsIjoiaHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYXBwbGUuY29tL2hvbWVwb2QvIiwiY29udGVudFV1aWQiOiIyMmUzZjBiNy1jMTc5LTM5MmEtODIxYy1lNmRmNTNjMjgwYTYifQ&amp;signature=AQAAAZLnR3S2KbD5Q6PLJUnEcdOnwGDQLbiRbs0LzN41wTFq&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.apple.com%2Fhomepod%2F">HomePod</a> is definitely worth considering. At $300, it&#39;s a lot cheaper than these Sonos speakers but supports spatial audio like the Era 300. The Era 300 and Sonos Five are better speakers overall (and certainly much louder), but there&#39;s a lot to like about the HomePod&#39;s audio quality at its price point. It&#39;s a clear, crisp vocal-forward speaker, and its design and software processing does a great job of making music sound like it&#39;s all around you, even if you&#39;re not playing back Dolby Atmos tracks.</p><h2> Best portable smart speaker: Sonos Roam </h2><p><core-commerce id="ad8441cad45a4faabcbc0e9b04740ef1" data-type="product-list"></core-commerce></p><p> While many people will be happy with a few speakers strategically placed throughout their home, you might want something that works outside as well as inside. Fortunately, you can find speakers that pair voice controls and strong music playback performance with portable, weatherproof form factors. For my money, it&#39;s hard to beat the <a data-i13n="cpos:13;pos:1;elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Sonos;elmt:;" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=1e71dc69-0ad7-47e7-abf5-dc3926557fa3&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Sonos&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsInN0b3JlSWQiOiIxZTcxZGM2OS0wYWQ3LTQ3ZTctYWJmNS1kYzM5MjY1NTdmYTMiLCJsYW5kaW5nVXJsIjoiaHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuc29ub3MuY29tL2VuLXVzL3Nob3Avcm9hbSIsImNvbnRlbnRVdWlkIjoiMjJlM2YwYjctYzE3OS0zOTJhLTgyMWMtZTZkZjUzYzI4MGE2In0&amp;signature=AQAAAeq2_H9R60wVGN9EP4TrWro8mlqbdOt9_4uJX6UE_CCp&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.sonos.com%2Fen-us%2Fshop%2Froam">Sonos Roam</a> for sheer versatility, not to mention audio quality.</p><p> When used inside the home, the Roam works like any other Sonos speaker. It fits in with an existing multi-room Sonos setup, or you can get a pair for stereo playback. Like most other Sonos speakers, it works with the Sonos Voice Assistant, Google Assistant or Amazon Alexa, and it supports essentially every major music service available. It sounds very good given its tiny size; it&#39;s quieter and not quite as clear as the Sonos One or the Era 100, but it still packs a surprising bass thump and distinct highs.</p><p> Since it was designed with on-the-go usage in mind, the Roam has a battery and Bluetooth so you can take it anywhere and use it far away from your WiFi network. And its diminutive size makes it easy to take it everywhere, both around the house and out and about. It&#39;s also the first Sonos speaker that is fully waterproof, as well as dust- and drop-resistant, so you shouldn&#39;t worry about taking it to the pool or beach.</p><p> The Roam gets about 10 hours of battery life, whether you&#39;re on WiFI or Bluetooth. There are other portable speakers that last longer, so if you&#39;re really going to push the battery you might be better served by another option.</p><p> Another wireless portable speaker option is the $449 <a data-i13n="elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Sonos;elmt:;cpos:14;pos:1" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=1e71dc69-0ad7-47e7-abf5-dc3926557fa3&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Sonos&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsImxhbmRpbmdVcmwiOiJodHRwczovL3d3dy5zb25vcy5jb20vZW4tdXMvc2hvcC9tb3ZlLTIiLCJjb250ZW50VXVpZCI6IjIyZTNmMGI3LWMxNzktMzkyYS04MjFjLWU2ZGY1M2MyODBhNiJ9&amp;signature=AQAAASZXj7NCTsNbpVKA0c7B-T3ECu1TAYuWww9ProYCD-IL&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.sonos.com%2Fen-us%2Fshop%2Fmove-2" class="rapid-with-clickid" data-original-link="https://www.sonos.com/en-us/shop/move-2">Sonos Move 2</a> . It&#39;s much larger and louder than the Roam, which is unsurprising given how much more expensive it is. It&#39;s a nice upgrade over the previous Move, with two tweeters for more detailed sound, a battery that lasts more than a day and redesigned touch controls up top. It also has a line-in jack via USB-C, so you can hook up a turntable when you&#39;re using it inside. If you&#39;re willing to sacrifice portability for power and better sound quality (and can afford it), the Move 2 will be more satisfying than the Roam.</p><p> A better choice than the Move, unless you already have other Sonos products, is the $399 <a data-i13n="cpos:15;pos:1;elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Amazon;elmt:;" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;&amp;signature=AQAAAcJ8lMPA4i0iXXFpC6cy2D1NxIuyoKaZL6BUuU7fBz7v&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2FBose-Portable-Home-Speaker-Built%2Fdp%2FB07VFKBQ3K%3Fth%3D1">Bose Portable Smart speaker</a> . It supports Alexa and Google Assistant commands, and since it can connect to WiFi, you can ask your preferred assistant to play music from Spotify, Amazon Music and other services. On top of that, it produces well-rounded sound, sports an IPX4 design with a convenient carry handle and will last up to 12 hours on a single charge.</p><p> Bose also has a good alternative to the Roam. The $149 <a data-i13n="cpos:16;pos:1;elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Amazon;elmt:;" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;&amp;signature=AQAAAWApfm9Tkcg4KZ_ozvq88khu_GJ_3edD8nKreQxBN7lX&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2FBose-SoundLink-Bluetooth-Portable-Waterproof%2Fdp%2FB099TJGJ91%3Fth%3D1">SoundLink Flex</a> supports Siri and Google Assistant commands, plus it has an IP67 design that&#39;s roughly the size of a small clutch bag. It pumps out bright, dynamic sound and can pair with other speakers for stereo sound, too – it&#39;s excellent and slightly cheaper than the Roam.</p><p> While this guide is all about smart speakers, we&#39;d be remiss if we didn&#39;t mention all of the solid portable speakers out there that either have limited smart features or none at all. We have <a data-i13n="cpos:17;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/best-portable-bluetooth-speakers-133004551.html">an entire guide</a> to the best portable Bluetooth speakers, so if you&#39;re purely concerned with portability and less about having an ecosystem of connected speakers, there are lots of options worth investigating.</p> This article originally appeared on Engadget at https://www.engadget.com/best-smart-speakers-151515264.html?src=rss]]>;</description><link/><![CDATA[https://www.engadget.com/best-smart-speakers-151515264.html?src=rss]]><source_id> engadget_479</source_id><guid ispermalink="false"> 22e3f0b7-c179-392a-821c-e6df53c280a6</guid><dc:creator> Nathan Ingraham</dc:creator><source/><![CDATA[Engadget]]><dc:publisher> Engadget</dc:publisher><dc:rightsholder> Engadget</dc:rightsholder><pubDate> Mon, 09 Oct 2023 14:30:41 +0000</pubDate><ingested> 1696861842</ingested><modified> 2023-10-09T14:30:57+00:00 </modified><category><![CDATA[amazon]]></category><category><![CDATA[BuyersGuide]]></category><category><![CDATA[smarthome2020]]></category><category><![CDATA[thebuyersguide]]></category><category><![CDATA[google]]></category><category><![CDATA[sonos]]></category><category><![CDATA[gear]]></category><category><![CDATA[home]]></category><category><![CDATA[ElectronicEquipment,Instruments&Components]]></category><category><![CDATA[Home&Garden]]></category><category><![CDATA[ElectronicsAccessories]]></category><category><![CDATA[Lifestyle(houseAndHome)]]></category><category><![CDATA[DIY&HomeImprovement]]></category><category><![CDATA[OfficeElectronics]]></category><category><![CDATA[Technology&Electronics]]></category><category><![CDATA[Speakers & Headphones]]></category><category><![CDATA[Audio Technology]]></category><category><![CDATA[Technology & Electronics]]></category><category><![CDATA[site|engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[provider_name|Engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[region|US]]></category><category><![CDATA[language|en-US]]></category><category><![CDATA[author_name|Nathan Ingraham]]></category><media:content height="1600" medium="image" url="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-03/a12ab710-cc29-11ed-abef-f71b78c368d5" width="2400"><media:keywords> headline </media:keywords><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[1]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[ ]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[ ]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[ ]]></media:title></media:content><media:content height="1600" medium="image" url="https://media-mbst-pub-ue1.s3.amazonaws.com/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-03/a12ab710-cc29-11ed-abef-f71b78c368d5" width="2400"><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[2]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[Photo by Nathan Ingraham / Engadget]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[The latest Sonos speaker, the Era 100]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[Sonos Era 100 smart speaker]]></media:title></media:content></item><item><title><![CDATA[How hackers are using Bluetooth to track police activity]]></title><description type="html"><![CDATA[<p> Cops use all sorts of tech to track individuals — <a data-i13n="cpos:1;pos:1" href="https://www.brookings.edu/articles/police-surveillance-and-facial-recognition-why-data-privacy-is-an-imperative-for-communities-of-color/">facial recognition comes to mind</a> , as does mimicking <a data-i13n="cpos:2;pos:1" href="https://www.sandiegouniontribune.com/sdut-police-technology-devices-surveillance-privacy-2015may21-story.html">cell phone towers to get pings</a> or <a data-i13n="cpos:3;pos:1" href="https://www.pbs.org/newshour/politics/how-an-obscure-cellphone-tracking-tool-provides-police-mass-surveillance-on-a-budget">mobile data tracking</a> . But some people are finding ways to use technology to listen back. Bluetooth signals might reveal where police are and when they are and when devices like body cams or Tasers are activated.</p><p> “It&#39;s be really weird if you had your volume turned all the way up and all of your devices are just screaming, right?,” Alan “Nullagent” Meekins, cofounder of Bluetooth tracking platform RFParty, said. “But that&#39;s really what you&#39;re doing in these wireless spectrums, they&#39;re just constantly shouting.”</p><span id="end-legacy-contents"></span><p> All Bluetooth devices have a unique 64 bit identifier called a MAC address. Often a chunk of that address is composed of an Organizational Unique Identifier (OUI), essentially a way for a device to say who it&#39;s made by. A look at the IoT devices that are used by many police forces led Meekins and his cofounder Roger “RekcahDam” Hicks to Axon, a company best known for Tasers. Modern police kits are overflowing with Bluetooth-enabled tech (often also made by Axon), from the aforementioned Tasers and body cams, to in-vehicle laptops. Even the gun holsters supplied to some cops send a Bluetooth ping when a sidearm is unholstered. By just reading company documentation, they were able to find the OUI.</p><p> A Bluetooth identifier seems trivial, but it could reveal a lot of information about where cops are and what they&#39;re up to, like when their body cams are recording or they turn on the sirens to respond to a call. “There&#39;s the signal that is sent when a police officer basically thinks something&#39;s recording worthy, if that&#39;s the case, people can document that, detect that and there won&#39;t be any question whether or not hey, there&#39;s a body cam or there wasn&#39;t body cam,” Meekins told Engadget. It&#39;s a way to potentially determine whether certain evidence exists so that it can be produced more quickly in a records request — something police often &quot;slow walk&quot; Meekins said. As people run RFParty, the app will collect historical data. In the case of body cams, if the device begins recording, it typically sends a Bluetooth signal out to other devices. If a cop turns on a camera (or Taser or other IoT device), someone running the app could collect this data to record details about the incident.</p><p> It&#39;s similar to radio waves: if you have the equipment to get past the music and news stations into the bands used by emergency response personnel (and once you know the language and <a data-i13n="cpos:4;pos:1" href="https://web.stanford.edu/~reneeb/bill/n.radio.code.html">codes to make sense of whats being broadcast there</a> ) you can listen in on cop radios to hear about arrests and where police might be patrolling.</p><p> An Axon spokesperson confirmed that the company uses Bluetooth capabilities for pairing in-car systems with mobile apps, and for its camera recording devices. Using Bluetooth connectivity helps with &quot;ensuring that incidents are captured and that devices are connected to maximize visibility,&quot; the spokesperson said. &quot;Axon is working on additional measures and improvements to address concerns of tracking our devices over time. Specifically, rotation of unique BLE device addresses (known as MAC addresses) that can specifically identify our devices, and removing the need for including serial numbers in Bluetooth broadcasts to reduce the ability to track a specific device over time.&quot;</p><p> No features in RFParty are designed specifically to track police, it&#39;s a general Bluetooth scanning service, similar to existing services like <a data-i13n="cpos:5;pos:1" href="https://www.wigle.net/">Wigle.net</a> or <a data-i13n="cpos:6;pos:1" href="https://www.nordicsemi.com/Products/Development-tools/nrf-connect-for-desktop">nRF Connect</a> . But some of what&#39;s displayed on its maps includes common Internet of Things devices used by police, including body cams. Anecdotally, <a data-i13n="cpos:7;pos:1" href="https://twitter.com/lozaning/status/1700679226502828144">users are already</a> using RFParty for police tracking purposes.</p><p> “We have all this technology that there&#39;s certain people who understand it, and can exploit it. But you know, most people can&#39;t and I think there needs to be more knowledge given out,” Hicks told Engadget. In <a data-i13n="cpos:8;pos:1" href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=cO1JSzAdPM8">a talk at DefCon 31 this past</a> August, Meekins showed what the Axon OUI is and privately provided a live demo to me of how a knowledgeable RFParty user could leverage that information.</p><p> Of course, having that historical data handy for accountability purposes requires people to be running RFParty in the vicinity of potential abuses of police power, and it&#39;s unlikely the app will become popular on a scale where that data will be available for almost any such incident. Still, when cops have the power to use technology against nearly anyone, it&#39;s interesting to see the tables turned.</p> This article originally appeared on Engadget at https://www.engadget.com/how-hackers-are-using-bluetooth-to-track-police-activity-140012717.html?src=rss]]>; </description><link/><![CDATA[https://www.engadget.com/how-hackers-are-using-bluetooth-to-track-police-activity-140012717.html?src=rss]]><source_id> engadget_479</source_id><guid ispermalink="false"> 0b3b99e8-7746-4738-9bbf-bcbf10ff484a</guid><dc:creator> Katie Malone</dc:creator><source/><![CDATA[Engadget]]><dc:publisher> Engadget</dc:publisher><dc:rightsholder> Engadget</dc:rightsholder><pubDate> Mon, 09 Oct 2023 14:00:12 +0000</pubDate><ingested> 1696860014</ingested><modified> 2023-10-09T14:00:21+00:00 </modified><category><![CDATA[Technology & Electronics]]></category><category><![CDATA[site|engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[provider_name|Engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[region|US]]></category><category><![CDATA[language|en-US]]></category><category><![CDATA[author_name|Katie Malone]]></category><media:content height="3264" medium="image" url="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2022-07/dfb83dc0-08e5-11ed-bff7-db9c7dfb46b3" width="4928"><media:keywords> headline </media:keywords><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[1]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[ ]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[ ]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[ ]]></media:title></media:content><media:content height="3264" medium="image" url="https://media-mbst-pub-ue1.s3.amazonaws.com/creatr-uploaded-images/2022-07/dfb83dc0-08e5-11ed-bff7-db9c7dfb46b3" width="4928"><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[2]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[artas via Getty Images]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[Close-up of police body camera]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[Close-up of police body camera]]></media:title></media:content></item><item><title><![CDATA[Watch NASA launch a mission to study a metal-rich asteroid this Thursday]]></title><description type="html"><![CDATA[<p> Despite what Jules Verne may have you believe, it&#39;s not exactly possible to <a data-i13n="cpos:1;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/2008-07-16-journey-to-the-center-of-the-earth-gained-more-revenue-from-3d-t.html">journey to the center of the Earth</a> . As such, it&#39;s pretty difficult to gain a full understanding of what the core of our planet looks like. <a data-i13n="cpos:2;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/tag/nasa/">NASA</a> is trying the next best thing.</p><p> It&#39;s set to launch a mission to an asteroid that&#39;s <a data-i13n="cpos:3;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/2019-06-12-nasa-psyche-mission-final-phase.html">understood to be largely made up of iron and nickel</a> . In fact, this metal-rich asteroid, which is called 16 Psyche, is believed to once have been part of a planetary core. This is the first NASA mission to study an asteroid that has more metal than rock or ice.</p><span id="end-legacy-contents"></span><p> Launch for the Psyche mission is <a data-i13n="cpos:4;pos:1" href="https://www.nasa.gov/news-release/nasa-sets-coverage-for-psyche-spacecraft-launch-to-metal-world/">targeted</a> for 10:16AM ET on Thursday. The spacecraft will launch <a data-i13n="cpos:5;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/2020-02-28-nasa-psyche-asteroid-mission-spacex.html">on a SpaceX Falcon Heavy rocket</a> from Kennedy Space Center in Florida (this will be the first of several NASA science missions in which the primary payload will launch on one of those rockets). You can watch a live stream of the launch below.</p><p> The Psyche spacecraft is around the size of a small van. As soon as it reaches the asteroid, it will start sending images of 16 Psyche back to Earth. It&#39;s equipped with a magnetometer, a gamma-ray and neutron spectrometer and a multispectral imager to study the asteroid. It will spend around two years snapping photos, mapping the asteroid&#39;s surface and collecting data to gain a better understanding of 16 Psyche&#39;s composition.</p><p> The spacecraft, which is powered by solar electric propulsion, is expected to reach 16 Psyche (which is in the main asteroid belt between Mars and Jupiter) in July 2029. If NASA had been ready to launch the mission last year, <a data-i13n="cpos:6;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/2017-05-24-nasa-psyche-asteroid-mission-fast-track.html">as was previously the plan</a> , it might have been able to reach 16 Psyche as early as 2026.</p><p> NASA understands that the 173-mile wide 16 Psyche asteroid may, in fact, not be an exposed core of a planetesimal, an early planetary building block. The agency <a data-i13n="cpos:7;pos:1" href="https://science.nasa.gov/mission/psyche/">says</a> that it might instead be the &quot;leftover piece of a completely different kind of iron-rich body that formed from metal-rich material somewhere in the solar system.&quot;</p><p> The spacecraft will have a second job to do. It will also test new laser communications tech from NASA JPL called <a data-i13n="cpos:8;pos:1" href="https://www.nasa.gov/solar-system/deep-space-optical-communications-dsoc/">Deep Space Optical Communications.</a> This is said to be able to transfer data and images at least 10 times faster than conventional systems. The experiment will test how capable the system is of transmitting data at faster rates beyond the Moon. However, it won&#39;t be used to send back any Psyche mission data. </p><div id="a4a8af043ed946d2b114ef86a53bbeab"><iframe src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/npIDMxrzm_o?rel=0" style="top:0;left:0;width:100%;height:100%;position:absolute;border:0;" allowfullscreen="" scrolling="no" data-embed-domain="www.youtube.com"></iframe></div><p></p> This article originally appeared on Engadget at https://www.engadget.com/watch-nasa-launch-a-mission-to-study-a-metal-rich-asteroid-this-thursday-133048930.html?src=rss]]>; </description><link/><![CDATA[https://www.engadget.com/watch-nasa-launch-a-mission-to-study-a-metal-rich-asteroid-this-thursday-133048930.html?src=rss]]><source_id> engadget_479</source_id><guid ispermalink="false"> 5b6a037a-9dd9-4f1b-8fb7-bfe316e32643</guid><dc:creator> Kris Holt</dc:creator><source/><![CDATA[Engadget]]><dc:publisher> Engadget</dc:publisher><dc:rightsholder> Engadget</dc:rightsholder><pubDate> Mon, 09 Oct 2023 13:30:48 +0000</pubDate><ingested> 1696858614</ingested><modified> 2023-10-09T13:37:03+00:00 </modified><category><![CDATA[Science]]></category><category><![CDATA[Space & Astronomy]]></category><category><![CDATA[site|engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[provider_name|Engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[region|US]]></category><category><![CDATA[language|en-US]]></category><category><![CDATA[author_name|Kris Holt]]></category><media:content height="1440" medium="image" url="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-10/d11a88a0-66a8-11ee-bfcf-d66298e73559" width="2385"><media:keywords> headline </media:keywords><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[1]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[ ]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[ ]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[ ]]></media:title></media:content><media:content height="1440" medium="image" url="https://media-mbst-pub-ue1.s3.amazonaws.com/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-10/d11a88a0-66a8-11ee-bfcf-d66298e73559" width="2385"><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[2]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[NASA]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[A rendering of NASA's Psyche spacecraft in space.]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[NASA's Psyche spacecraft]]></media:title></media:content></item><item><title><![CDATA[The Morning After: ChatGPT creator OpenAI might start making its own AI chips]]></title><description type="html"><![CDATA[<p> According to <em>Reuters</em> , OpenAI is <a data-i13n="cpos:1;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/openai-is-reportedly-considering-making-its-own-chips-113010353.html">exploring</a> making its own artificial intelligence chips, even looking into an acquisition. OpenAI CEO Sam Altman previously blamed GPU shortages for users&#39; concerns regarding the company API&#39;s speed and reliability, leading to these moves. OpenAI using its own chips could reduce its costs too. Based on analysis by Bernstein Research, each ChatGPT query costs the company around four cents.</p><p> At the moment, NVIDIA controls the market for chips that power AI applications. The Microsoft supercomputer OpenAI used to develop its technology, for instance, uses 10,000 NVIDIA GPUs. Microsoft, OpenAI&#39;s biggest backer, has been working on its own AI chip since 2019.</p><p> — Mat Smith </p><div id="a862de90ee4f41eebe885871b09023a2"><iframe src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/EsVrFByD5JE?rel=0&amp;start=60" style="top:0;left:0;width:100%;height:100%;position:absolute;border:0;" allowfullscreen="" scrolling="no" data-embed-domain="www.youtube.com"></iframe></div><p> <strong>The biggest stories you might have missed</strong></p><p> <a data-i13n="cpos:2;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/the-talos-principle-2-is-the-ideal-blend-of-puzzle-and-story-150009663.html">The Talos Principle 2 is the ideal blend of puzzle and story</a></p><p> <a data-i13n="cpos:3;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/amazons-first-internet-satellite-launch-was-a-success-202130763.html">Amazon&#39;s first internet satellite launch was a success</a></p><p> <a data-i13n="cpos:4;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/ios-17-review-notable-new-features-and-streamlined-touches-140009954.html">iOS 17 review: Notable new features and streamlined touches</a></p><p> <a data-i13n="cpos:5;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/hitting-the-books-the-six-loren-grush-scribner-143032524.html">Hitting the Books: NASA&#39;s Kathy Sullivan and advances in orbital personal hygiene</a></p><p> <a data-i13n="cpos:6;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/uk-regulator-says-snaps-ai-chatbot-may-put-kids-privacy-at-risk-145413931.html">UK regulator says Snap&#39;s AI chatbot may put kids&#39; privacy at risk</a></p><p>​​ <em>You can get these reports delivered daily direct to your inbox.</em> <a data-i13n="cpos:7;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/about/newsletter/"><em>Subscribe right here!</em></a>​​</p><p></p><h2> <a data-i13n="cpos:8;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/nasa-will-reveal-what-osiris-rex-brought-back-from-asteroid-bennu-on-wednesday-213651949.html">NASA will reveal on Wednesday what OSIRIS-REx brought back from asteroid Bennu</a></h2><h3> A first look at its asteroid sample.</h3> <a href="https://www.engadget.com/nasa-will-reveal-what-osiris-rex-brought-back-from-asteroid-bennu-on-wednesday-213651949.html"><figure><img src="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-10/9d295b30-6689-11ee-9fd7-f0232da3bd56" data-crop-orig-src="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-10/9d295b30-6689-11ee-9fd7-f0232da3bd56" style="height:450px;width:675px;" alt="TMA" data-uuid="c1b9faf7-50bc-3811-a4f3-10c5478c6687"><figcaption></figcaption> <div class="photo-credit">NASA/Keegan Barber</div></figure></a><p> NASA will give the public a look at the asteroid sample brought back to Earth by its OSIRIS-REx spacecraft. A livestream of the reveal is set for 11 AM ET on Wednesday, October 11. OSIRIS-REx grabbed its sample from Bennu back in 2020, then spent a year-and-a-half observing the asteroid before returning to Earth in May 2021. “The very best &#39;problem&#39; to have is that there is so much material, it&#39;s taking longer than we expected to collect it,” said Christopher Snead, NASA&#39;s deputy OSIRIS-REx curation lead.</p><p> <a data-i13n="cpos:9;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/nasa-will-reveal-what-osiris-rex-brought-back-from-asteroid-bennu-on-wednesday-213651949.html"><strong>Continue reading.</strong></a></p><p></p><h2> <a data-i13n="cpos:10;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/atari-is-releasing-a-new-cartridge-for-its-46-year-old-2600-console-183922523.html">Atari is releasing a new cartridge for its 46-year-old 2600 console</a></h2><h3> Save Mary never hit store shelves.</h3><h3></h3><p> Atari just announced pre-orders for a physical cartridge of the company&#39;s once-ubiquitous 2600 console. The game, <em>Save Mary</em> , was developed during the console&#39;s golden years, before being shelved when the 2600 went the way of the dodo. If you want to play it, you don&#39;t need to dust down your old 2600. Conveniently, Atari sells an upgraded version of the console, <a data-i13n="cpos:11;pos:1" href="https://atari.com/products/atari-2600-plus">called the 2600+.</a> What a relief.</p><p> <a data-i13n="cpos:12;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/atari-is-releasing-a-new-cartridge-for-its-46-year-old-2600-console-183922523.html"><strong>Continue reading.</strong></a></p><p></p><h2> <a data-i13n="cpos:13;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/x-tests-three-paid-subscription-tiers-amid-ongoing-financial-woes-164120812.html">X tests three paid subscription tiers</a></h2><h3> It looks like this will determine how many ads you see.</h3><h3></h3><p> <em>Bloomberg</em> reports that X is testing a trio of subscription tiers to help solve its financial woes. Details are scant, but these paid subscription options are likely to impact the number of ads you might see when using the platform. It looks like it&#39;ll break down into Basic, Standard and Plus. Basic users will continue to see the regular number of ads, while standard users will see half, equivalent to what folks who pay $8 each month get at the moment. Plus users will see no ads whatsoever, for however much that might cost.</p><p> <a data-i13n="cpos:14;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/x-tests-three-paid-subscription-tiers-amid-ongoing-financial-woes-164120812.html"><strong>Continue reading.</strong></a></p><p></p><span id="end-legacy-contents"></span><h2> <a data-i13n="cpos:15;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/engadget-podcast-google-pixel-8-phones-pixel-watch-2-172659855.html">Engadget Podcast: Google&#39;s Pixel 8 phones and Pixel Watch 2</a></h2><h3> And Samsung launched even more devices.</h3> <a href="https://www.engadget.com/engadget-podcast-google-pixel-8-phones-pixel-watch-2-172659855.html"><figure><img src="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-10/e84247a0-6687-11ee-bed6-c7d7daa87c90" data-crop-orig-src="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-10/e84247a0-6687-11ee-bed6-c7d7daa87c90" style="height:303px;width:675px;" alt="TMA" data-uuid="27b75e14-cf3a-38f8-aed1-2108e94d4683"><figcaption></figcaption> <div class="photo-credit">Engadget</div></figure></a><p> This week, Cherlynn and Devindra chat with Engadget&#39;s Sam Rutherford about everything from the Made by Google event. That includes the Pixel 8, Pixel 8 Pro and Pixel Watch 2. We give Google credit for leaning on AI long before it was trendy, but we wonder if the Pixel 8 Pro&#39;s temperature sensor will actually be useful.</p><p> <a data-i13n="cpos:16;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/engadget-podcast-google-pixel-8-phones-pixel-watch-2-172659855.html%20https://www.engadget.com/..."><strong>Listen here.</strong></a></p><h3></h3> This article originally appeared on Engadget at https://www.engadget.com/the-morning-after-chatgpt-creator-openai-might-start-making-its-own-ai-chips-111521672.html?src=rss]]>; </description><link/><![CDATA[https://www.engadget.com/the-morning-after-chatgpt-creator-openai-might-start-making-its-own-ai-chips-111521672.html?src=rss]]><sour